Why late 2023/early 2024?
*   The author is reflecting on the "sedate" pace of Rust innovation post-2023.
*   The mention of C++26 as a future standard with specific features (stackful coroutines) suggests the author is looking ahead from a point where C++23 is either just out or about to be finalized. C++23 was finalized in March 2023. By late 2023, discussions about C++26 were beginning to gain traction in proposal forums.
*   The frustration with Cargo’s monoculture and the desire for CMake is a recurring theme in the Rust C++ migration debates, which saw a surge in 2023–2024.

